data.title: COUNTY BY COUNTY: Lake-effect snow set to impact Central New York
data.meta_description: Our Spectrum News 1 Weather Experts have broken down, by county, what to watch for.
data.text:
Our Spectrum News 1 Weather Experts have broken down, by county, what to watch for as a lake-effect snow event impacts the region through Monday. For the latest forecast updates, you can check here.

Main impact: No further impacts

Additional snowfall: None

Wind gusts: Up to 15 mph

Main impact: Through midday Monday

Additional snowfall: Up to 2 inches

Wind gusts: Up to 30 mph

Winter Storm Warning (until 1 p.m. Monday)

Main impact: Through Monday morning afternoon

Additional snowfall: 4 to 8 inches, locally higher

Wind gusts: Up to 30 mph

Main impact: No further impacts

Additional snowfall: None

Wind gusts: Up to 15 mph

Winter Storm Warning (until 1 p.m. Monday)

Main impact: Through Monday morning

Additional snowfall: 1 to 4 inches north

Wind gusts: Up to 20 mph

Winter Storm Warning (until 7 p.m. Monday)

Main impact: Through Monday morning

Additional snowfall: 4 to 8 inches

Wind gusts: Up to 20 mph
